# {{DOMAIN}} Wiki — Schema & Workflows

This is the rulebook for the {{DOMAIN}} wiki. It turns Claude from a generic chatbot into a disciplined wiki maintainer. Read fully at session start; do not skim.

**Generated:** {{DATE}}
**ADR log:** `docs/schema-decisions.md`

---

## Purpose

{{PURPOSE}}

The wiki is **persistent external memory for agents and humans**. Every research session preserves source material at multiple levels of detail. Agents can navigate from high-level summaries down to verbatim source text without re-fetching anything from the web.

## Three-tier storage model

This wiki stores source material at three levels. Agents should choose the right tier for their task:

| Tier | Location | What it contains | When to use |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Summary** | `wiki/` entity pages | Curated claims, open questions, strategic implications | Orientation, quick answers, entity relationships |
| **Synthesis** | `wiki/digests/` | Structured claims with `→ [[entity]]` links, scope/purpose of source | Connecting sources to entities, understanding what was captured |
| **Raw** | `raw/` | Original source material at full fidelity | Last-mile context, exact wording, agent reasoning at depth |

Within `raw/`:
- `raw/research-*.md` — agent-synthesized research with structured findings + citations
- `raw/snapshots/*.txt` — **verbatim accessibility tree captures** of individual web pages (full text of the source at capture time)
- `raw/assets/screenshots/*.png` — visual captures of pages
- `raw/MANIFEST.md` — catalog of all sources with ingest status

**For agents doing precise analysis:** read the entity page for orientation, then go to `raw/snapshots/` for the exact source text. This avoids re-fetching and preserves the information as it existed at capture time.

