## Hard rules

1. `raw/` is immutable. Never modify files in `raw/`. Exceptions: you may write to `raw/_ingest/` (transactional plan files) and `raw/_scrubbed/` (pre-scrub output). Both are gitignored.
2. No PII in `wiki/` or `wiki/digests/`. See `## PII scrub` for the two-stage gate.
3. Every entity page has required frontmatter + Overview + Open questions. No exceptions.
4. Wikilinks only in frontmatter `sources`/`related`. Use relative paths only for `raw/` assets.
5. Dates live in frontmatter (`last-updated`, `quarter`, `ingested`), not in filenames. Exception: decisions and experiments use date-prefix in filename.
6. New section headings must match the style guide (§ Style guide). Do not invent synonyms.
7. Before writing a page, run `python3 scripts/lint.py --check-content <path> --wiki-root .` to gate PII.
8. Frontmatter must be VALID YAML — Obsidian's Dataview rejects the whole block on syntax errors. Wikilink lists use multi-line form with quoted items.

