## Frontmatter

Every entity page has this frontmatter shape (multi-line YAML is required for wikilink lists):

```yaml
type: <one of the entity types above>
status: active | archived | superseded | draft | running | complete | shipped | planned | deprecated | cancelled | reversed
last-updated: YYYY-MM-DD
quarter: YYYY-QN
okr: []
confidence: high | med | low
sources:
  - "[[digest-slug]]"
related:
  - "[[slug]]"
tags: [topic-tag]
```

**`summary:`** Required for entity and question pages. Write as an answer-preview — what question does this page answer, not what the document is.
- ❌ `"Shopify competitor analysis"` — bibliographic, useless for navigation
- ✅ `"Shopify: 70+ reports all plans; ShopifyQL query language; no Z report capability"` — answers "what does Shopify offer?"

Minimum 40 chars. lint.py warns if missing or too short.

Synthesis pages (index, overview, glossary, people, _health) add `as-of: YYYY-MM-DD`.
Source digests add `source-path`, `ingested`, `pii-workflow`, and (if pre-scrub) `scrub-approved-by`, `scrub-approved-at`.

