## MANIFEST.md line format

Each source in `raw/MANIFEST.md` is one list item under a date-headed section:

```
- [ ] `<filename>` — <category> • <sensitivity> — pending-ingest
- [x] `<filename>` — <category> • <sensitivity> — ingested YYYY-MM-DD → wiki/digests/<slug>.md
- [ ] `<filename>` — <category> • <sensitivity> — blocked: pii — flagged at lines L1,L2,...
```

State transitions: pending-ingest → ingested (on scrub-pass) | blocked:pii (on scrub-fail). Edit the line in place; do not append duplicates.

---

## Log format

```
## [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] <verb> — [[slug]] | touched: [p1, p2, ...] | <summary>
```

Verbs: `ingest | query | lint | scrub | rewrite | archive | scaffold | session` (`session` is written by `/session-close`). Log files: `wiki/log/YYYY-QN.md`, one per quarter.

## Claim tags & trust markup

Every numeric claim in body prose (currency, percentages, magnitudes,
multipliers, integers ≥ 3 digits) must sit in a paragraph carrying at least
one of: a source tag (`[internal::file]`, `[internal::data]`,
`[external::web-search]`, `[external::claude-knowledge]`), a `[[wikilink]]`
to the backing page, a URL, `[hypothesis]`, `[verified: YYYY-MM-DD]`, or
`[REFUTED]`. Lint enforces this (error). To suppress a false positive, add
`%%[no-claim]%%` to the paragraph — invisible in Obsidian reading view,
greppable in source. Dates, quarters, versions, and bare years never count
as claims.

Trust markup: mark fact-checked claims `[verified: YYYY-MM-DD]`, unvalidated
ones `[hypothesis]`, and disproven ones ~~struck through~~ with `[REFUTED]`.
Lint maintains a visible `> Trust: N verified · N hypothesis · N refuted`
line under each marked page's title, and the index catalog shows the ratio.

Readability: initiative, segment, and content-synthesis pages open with a
`## Bottom line` section (2-4 sentences of position, not topic description).
`overview.md` must keep `## Current theses` populated — a link list is not
an overview. Source-less pages are capped at `confidence: low`.
